\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces High-level \textsc  {clawOS}{} architecture. The Rust-based microkernel (blue) provides scheduling, IPC, capabilities, and memory management. Three user-space servers handle domain-specific functionality: \textsc  {EvoClaw}{} (green) for agent evolution, \textsc  {ClawChain}{} (purple) for blockchain identity/economics, and the Trading Engine (orange) for market operations. Agents run as first-class processes with genome metadata, on-chain identity, and economic accounts. Dashed pink lines indicate cross-server IPC communication.}}{7}{figure.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{1}{7}{High-level \clawos {} architecture. The Rust-based microkernel (blue) provides scheduling, IPC, capabilities, and memory management. Three user-space servers handle domain-specific functionality: \evoclaw {} (green) for agent evolution, \clawchain {} (purple) for blockchain identity/economics, and the Trading Engine (orange) for market operations. Agents run as first-class processes with genome metadata, on-chain identity, and economic accounts. Dashed pink lines indicate cross-server IPC communication}{figure.caption.2}{}}
